יוִכְשֶׂ / bird of dawn has been variously rendered as "rooster," "watchman,"
"celestial appearance," or "meteor." In an urban setting, the earliest sound
of life we are likely to hear at dawn is the chirping of sparrows. /ITSeh/±vi/XX is
thus rendered differently from /ITgever/XX, rooster, here to capture some of the
ambiguity of the word.    /SC/XXJ.R./XX/PR

