/PG166/XX/PR

As long as spirit breathes in me, I offer thanks before you,
/SCB/XXREATH /XXD/XXIVINE/XX, my God, God of my ancestors, the master of
all deeds, and source of every life. Blessed are you, /SCT/XXHE /XXH/XXOLY
/XXS/XXPIRIT/XX, in whose possession is the breath of every living thing,
the animation of all flesh./PR

/SCK/XXAVANAH/XX. We are each created in the image of God. When we allow the
reflections of our own beings to illuminate the universe, when we under-
stand that we carry God /ITwithin us/XX, we are closer to doing the work that
will eventually perfect the world. When we each accept the purity of our
own souls and the purity of the souls of others, /ITtikun olam/XX will have been
achieved.    /SC/XXL.B./XX/PR

/PR

/SCK/XXAVANAH/XX. "Sleep is one sixtieth a part of death (Talmud Berah/±ot 57b),"
and waking is a kind of rebirth.    /SC/XXL.W.K./XX/PR

